11.commit_message: Bug 1509420: Handle CCWs of functions properly in bindToAsyncStack shell function. r=jorendorff  In js.cpp, BindToAsyncStack used JSObject::isCallable to check the type of its argument, and then BoundToAsyncStack (the native for the function returned) assumed that it could call JSObject::as<JSFunction> on that value.  However, there are many things that are isCallable but not is<JSFunction>, two examples being CCWs and function proxies.  Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D14343
